The standard fix is:

```java
public XmlDeclaration asXmlDeclaration() {
    String data = getData();
    String declContent = data;
    boolean isProcessingInstruction = false;
    if (data.startsWith("?")) {
        // Processing instruction: <? ... ?>
        declContent = data.substring(1, data.length() - 1);
        isProcessingInstruction = true;
    } else if (data.startsWith("!")) {
        // Declaration: <! ... >
        declContent = data.substring(1); // note: may not have trailing ?
    } else {
        return null; // not a valid declaration
    }
    Document doc = Jsoup.parse("<" + declContent + ">", baseUri(), Parser.xmlParser());
    if (doc.childNodeSize() > 0) {
        Element el = doc.child(0);
        XmlDeclaration decl = new XmlDeclaration(NodeUtils.parser(doc).settings().normalizeTag(el.tagName()), isProcessingInstruction);
        decl.attributes().addAll(el.attributes());
        return decl;
    }
    return null;
}
```

